{{Infobox scientist | image = <!-- only free-content images are allowed for depicting living people - see [[WP:NONFREE]] --> | image_size = 150px | name = Arcadio Poveda | birth_date = 15 July 1930 | birth_place = [[Mérida, Yucatán]] <ref name="colegio">{{cite web | author = El Colegio Nacional | title = Miembros: Poveda Ricalde, Arcadio | url = http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/content.aspx?se=vida&te=detallemiembro&mi=138 | language = Spanish | accessdate = 2008-06-08 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080917062549/http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/content.aspx?se=vida&te=detallemiembro&mi=138 | archivedate = 2008-09-17 | df = }}</ref> | residence = [[Mexico City]] | nationality = Mexican | field = Astronomy | work_institution = [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]] | alma_mater = [[University of California, Berkeley]]<ref name="curriculum">{{cite web|first=Arcadio |last=Poveda |title=Curriculum vitae |url=http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/pdf/1989/06%20-%20Arcadio%20Poveda%20Ricalde_%20Curriculum%20vitae.pdf |language=Spanish |accessdate=2008-06-10 |format=PDF |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606071403/http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/pdf/1989/06%20-%20Arcadio%20Poveda%20Ricalde_%20Curriculum%20vitae.pdf |archivedate=2011-06-06 }}</ref> | doctoral_advisor = | known_for = Poveda's formula<ref name="ar">{{cite web |first = James |last = Binney | title= Dynamics of Elliptical Galaxies and Other Spheroidal Components | publisher = Annual Reviews | date = 1982 | url = http://nedwww.ipac.caltech.edu/level5/March04/Binney/Binney3_2.html | accessdate = 2008-06-10 }}</ref> | prizes = [[National Prize for Arts and Science]] (Mexico, 1975) | footnotes = }}
'''Renán Arcadio Poveda Ricalde''' (born 15 July 1930) is a prominent [[Mexico|Mexican]] [[Astronomy|astronomer]] who developed a method to calculate the mass of [[elliptical galaxy|elliptical galaxies]].<ref name="colegio"/> He received Mexico's [[National Prize for Arts and Sciences]] in 1975, chaired its National Astronomical Observatory from 1968 to 1980 and was elected to [[Colegio Nacional (Mexico)|The National College]] in 1989.<ref name="curriculum"/>
Poveda was born in [[Mérida, Yucatán]]. He initially enrolled at the [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]] but ended up graduating with both a Bachelor of Arts degree (1953) and a [[PhD]] in [[Astronomy]] (1956) from the [[University of California, Berkeley]].<ref name ="curriculum"/> Afterward, he moved back to Mexico and enrolled at the Institute of Astronomy of the National Autonomous University, where he has worked as a researcher since 1956. As a visiting scholar, he has lectured at the Institute of Astrophysics in [[France]] ([[CNRS]], 1963), [[Columbia University]] (1967), [[Kitt Peak National Observatory]] (1981–82, 1983–84), and at the [[University of California, San Diego]] (1982–83).<ref name="curriculum"/>
A public [[planetarium]] in his native [[Mérida, Yucatán]], is named in his honor.<ref name="merida">{{cite web |author=Municipality of Mérida | title = Planetario Arcadio Poveda | url = http://www.merida.gob.mx/planetario/principal.htm | language = Spanish | accessdate = 2008-06-10 | archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080606034230/http://www.merida.gob.mx/planetario/principal.htm| archivedate= 6 June 2008 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref>
