'''''Enterobacteria phage T6''''' is a [[bacteriophage]] that infects [[Escherichia coli]] bacteria. It was one bacteriophage that was used as a model system in the 1950s in exploring the methods viruses replicate, along with the other [[T-even bacteriophages]]: [[Enterobacteria phage T4]] and [[Enterobacteria phage T2]].<ref>[http://m.eb.com/topic/48324 ''Encyclopædia Britannica'']</ref>

