===Lesser Sunda Islands===
The [[Lesser Sunda Islands]] is a small [[archipelago]] which, from west to east, consists of [[Bali]], [[Lombok]], [[Sumbawa]], [[Flores]], [[Sumba]] and the [[Timor]] islands; all are located at the edge of the [[continental shelf|Australian continental shelf]]. Volcanoes in the area are formed because of [[oceanic crust]]s and the movement of the shelf itself.<ref>{{cite journal|author=H. A. Brouwer|title=Exploration in the Lesser Sunda Islands|journal=The Geographical Journal|volume=94|issue=1|pages=1&ndash;10|date=July 1939|doi=10.2307/1788584|jstor=1788584|publisher=Blackwell Publishing}}</ref> Some volcanoes completely form an island, for instance, the [[Sangeang Api]] island. [[Mount Tambora]], on Sumbawa island, erupted on 5 April 1815, with a scale 7 on the [[Volcanic Explosivity Index|VEI]] and is considered the most violent eruption in recorded history.<ref name="Stothers1984"/>

