'''''Sociological Theory''''' is a peer-reviewed journal published by [[SAGE Publications]] for the [[American Sociological Association]]. The journal's purpose is to cover the full breadth of sociological theory.<ref name=sage>{{cite web|title=Sociological Theory|url=http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal201997?q=sociological%20theory&productType=Journals&fs=1#tabview=aimsAndScope|publisher=SAGE|accessdate=3 July 2017}}</ref> The [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Mustafa Emirbayer]] ([[University of Wisconsin-Madison]]). According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2017 [[impact factor]] of 2.156, ranking it 26th out of 146 journals in the category "Sociology".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Sociology |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
