{{italic title}} '''''Wonder Why?''''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] educational television program for children, produced by [[CTV Atlantic|ATV]] in [[Halifax Regional Municipality|Halifax, Nova Scotia]] and aired nationally by [[CTV Television Network|CTV]] between 1990 and 1994. The program starred then-ATV chief [[meteorologist]] [[Richard Zurawski]] as the host and Liam Hyland as the young detective Question Mark. Running for 4 seasons, the Maritime-based science show won the CanPro Award each year for Best Educational Show for children. Each episode examined topics related to science, technology, and everyday items or processes.
==External links== *{{IMDb title|id=0481259|title=Wonder Why}} *[http://www.broadcasting-history.ca/programming/television/programming_popup.php?id=236 ''Wonder Why?'' on broadcasting-history.ca]
